Package edu.up.cs301.tictactoe

Interface Summary
TTTGame An interface that implements a tic-tac-toe game
TTTPlayer An interface that defines a tic-tac-toe game player.
 

Class Summary
TTTComputerPlayer A computerized (automated) tic-tac-toe player.
TTTComputerPlayer1 This is a really dumb computer player that always just makes a random move it's so stupid that it sometimes tries to make moves on non-blank spots.
TTTComputerPlayer2 A computerized tic-tac-toe player that recognizes an immediate win or loss, and plays appropriately.
TTTHumanPlayer A human (i.e., GUI) version of a tic-tac-toe player.
TTTHumanPlayer1 A GUI that allows a human to play tic-tac-toe.
TTTHumanPlayer2 A human (i.e., GUI) version of a tic-tac-toe player.
TTTHumanPlayer3 A human (i.e., GUI) version of a tic-tac-toe player that gives the user the "game of 33" view.
TTTLocalGame The TTTLocalGame class for a simple tic-tac-toe game.
TTTMainActivity this is the primary activity for Counter game
TTTMoveAction A game-move object that a tic-tac-toe player sends to the game to make a move.
TTTState Contains the state of a Tic-Tac-Toe game.
